      "type": "description",
      "value": {
        "latex": "On considère un système linéaire homogène : $(S) \\iff AX = 0$, avec\n$A \\in \\mathcal{M}_{n,p}(K)$, $n < p$ et $\\mathrm{rg} A = n$.",
        "html": "<p>On considère un système linéaire homogène : <span class=\"math inline\">\\((S) \\iff AX = 0\\)</span>, avec <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A \\in \\mathcal{M}_{n,p}(K)\\)</span>, <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n &lt; p\\)</span> et <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\mathrm{rg} A = n\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "472ccf9a-3fe5-426a-a3fb-7e0911503274",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer qu'on peut compléter $A$ en une matrice\n     $B = \\begin{pmatrix} A \\cr A' \\cr \\end{pmatrix}$ inversible.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer qu’on peut compléter <span class=\"math inline\">\\(A\\)</span> en une matrice <span class=\"math inline\">\\(B = \\begin{pmatrix} A \\cr A&#39; \\cr \\end{pmatrix}\\)</span> inversible.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "a5dfcce0-115b-424b-a114-0b33578bd0ab",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Montrer que les colonnes $n+1$ à $p$ de ${}^{t\\!}\\text{com}\\, B$ constituent\n     une base des solutions de $(S)$.",
        "html": "<p>Montrer que les colonnes <span class=\"math inline\">\\(n+1\\)</span> à <span class=\"math inline\">\\(p\\)</span> de <span class=\"math inline\">\\({}^{t\\!}\\text{com}\\, B\\)</span> constituent une base des solutions de <span class=\"math inline\">\\((S)\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "31cfbe29-a48b-4bb8-be74-451bd81c071c",
      "type": "question",
      "value": {
        "latex": "Consid\\'erer l'exemple suivant : \n  $$(S) \\iff \\left\\{\n  \\begin{array} {lllllllll}\n  x &+& 2y &+& 3z &+& 4t &=& 0  \\cr\n 2x &+& 3y &+& 4z &+& 5t &=& 0. \\cr\n \\end{array}\n \\right.$$",
        "html": "<p>Considérer l’exemple suivant : <span class=\"math display\">\\[(S) \\iff \\left\\{\n  \\begin{array} {lllllllll}\n  x &amp;+&amp; 2y &amp;+&amp; 3z &amp;+&amp; 4t &amp;=&amp; 0  \\cr\n 2x &amp;+&amp; 3y &amp;+&amp; 4z &amp;+&amp; 5t &amp;=&amp; 0. \\cr\n \\end{array}\n \\right.\\]</span></p>\n"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "9d8274a9-e805-4b53-9b6e-4e5b9a586c30",
      "type": "reponse",
      "value": {
        "latex": "3. On complète par $\\begin{pmatrix} 0 & 0 & 1 & 0 \\cr 0 & 0 & 0 & 1 \\cr \\end{pmatrix}\n               \\Rightarrow \\text{base} =\n               \\left\\{\\,\n               \\left(\\begin{smallmatrix} -1 \\cr 2 \\cr -1 \\cr 0 \\cr \\end{smallmatrix}\\right),\n               \\left(\\begin{smallmatrix} -2 \\cr 3 \\cr 0 \\cr -1 \\cr \\end{smallmatrix}\\right)\n               \\,\\right\\}$.",
        "html": "<p>3. On complète par <span class=\"math inline\">\\(\\begin{pmatrix} 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 \\cr 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 \\cr \\end{pmatrix}\n               \\Rightarrow \\text{base} =\n               \\left\\{\\,\n               \\left(\\begin{smallmatrix} -1 \\cr 2 \\cr -1 \\cr 0 \\cr \\end{smallmatrix}\\right),\n               \\left(\\begin{smallmatrix} -2 \\cr 3 \\cr 0 \\cr -1 \\cr \\end{smallmatrix}\\right)\n               \\,\\right\\}\\)</span>.</p>\n"
      }
    }
